solution.p:
We can begin by plotting the points that are easy to read off the diagram.
\begin{array}{c|c|c} x&f(x)&\frac{1}{f(x)}\\ \hline -3&-3&\frac{-1}{3}\\ -2&0&UND\\ -1&3&\frac{1}{3}\\ 0&3&\frac{1}{3}\\ 1&\frac{3}{2}&\frac{2}{3}\\ 2&0&UND\\ 3&1&1 \end{array}
Note that \frac{1}{f(x)} is undefined when f(x) = 0. So \frac{1}{f(x)} is undefined at x=-2 and x=2. We shall look more closely at the behaviour of \frac{1}{f(x)} for x near \pm 2 shortly.

